# Prototyper Project Rules

## Project Structure
- `backend/` - FastAPI REST API
- `frontend/` - Next.js application

## Development Workflow
- Update API client (`frontend/lib/api.ts`) when adding backend endpoints
- Keep frontend and backend interfaces in sync
- All components are kept under components/[feature]/
- Each component is placed in a separate file; no default export

## Documentation
- Read from prd.md to get the context of the requirements of the application if available
- Update README.md in frontend/backend respectively when adding major features
- Keep setup instructions current

## Code Review Standards
- New components should be reusable
- API endpoints must return proper status codes
- Use logger decorators to log major functions in the backend